sshc v5.0 - README [SSH Management Console]


Description :
when number of accesses to ssh gets high, managment gets hard, so in this time you can use this program for managing servers. By using this program you can select your server from menu and connect to server without password or add public ip address to server's firewall (iptables).


Dependencies :
0. openssl
1. sshpass
2. mkdir
3. cp
4. rm
5. whoami
6. ping
7. curl
8. ssh
9. nano
10. cat


Check dependencies :
0. chmod +x install.sh
1. sudo ./install.sh -c


Install sshc v5.0 :
0. chmod +x install.sh
1. sudo ./install.sh -i


Usage sshc v5.0 :
0. run program and edit your database
1. run program and connect to your servers


Uninstall sshc v5.0 :
0. sudo rm -rf /opt/sshc_v4/
1. sudo rm -f /usr/bin/sshc


Tested sshc on :
0. LMDE2 mate desktop - 3.16.0-4-amd64
1. chromixium 1.5 - 3.13.0-66-generic


Notes:
0. run this program just using root user or sudo
1. defaul password is 'sshc'
2. run program and edit your database
3. Special thanks to Mickael Dorigny from www.it-connect.fr for find new bug
